description: A chic and intimate space living up to its name. This is one of the best spots in Sai Gon to enjoy drinks as the sun sets over Park and Ben Thanh Market. Offering 270-degree city views, the environment created is the best of all worlds. “Luxuriously high enough up to delight in exquisitely romantic views of Park in its entirety, yet close enough to feel at eye level and at one with the city streets and rooftops. description:
Nestled along the scenic Saigon River, Latest Recipe at Le Méridien Saigon invites you to explore a vibrant world of flavors in one of Ho Chi Minh City’s most dynamic dining venues. With a contemporary setting and a captivating open kitchen, our restaurant showcases the artistry of live cooking—from fresh seafood and hand-pulled noodles to wood-fired pizzas and made-to-order specialties.

Delight in our international buffet, available daily for breakfast, lunch, dinner, and our indulgent Sunday brunch—each month showcasing a unique culinary theme inspired by flavors from around the world. For a more personalized experience, explore our thoughtfully crafted à la carte menu. Whether you’re celebrating with family, meeting friends, or hosting a business meal, Latest Recipe offers the perfect blend of global cuisine, warm service, and a lively yet elegant atmosphere.

The Monkey Gallery DINING is one of the first fine dining restaurants in Ho Chi Minh City, opening in 2019 with a passion for bringing a new gastronomic destination with a Vietnamese soul to local and international diners. The dining room features an ultra-high ceiling with a central open kitchen that acts as the heart of the gallery, where our artists work on their imaginative creations. description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description: About Anan Saigon: The name of the restaurant is ănăn, which also means ‘eat eat’. It is located in Chợ Cũ Tôn Thất Đạm, a wet market right in the center of bustling Saigon. We specialize in street food-inspired dishes created by the award-winning chef Peter Cuong Franklin. Chef Peter’s creative Vietnamese cuisine reflects his vision of a Vietnam that is deeply respectful of its history and traditions yet progressive and international in its outlook. He takes inspiration from the country’s vibrant food culture and uses fresh ingredients often sourced from local markets while incorporating French culinary techniques. The result is a focused menu of deeply flavorsome dishes that are all intended to pair perfectly with our bar’s diverse selection of local craft beers, carefully curated wines, and tropical inspired cocktails.

description: From the Opera House, walk along Dong Khoi street and you will easily recognize Saigon Café restaurant from its floor-to-ceiling glasses, luxury ambiance, modern finishing’s and vibrant energy. Situated on level 1 of the Sheraton Saigon Grand Opera Hotel overlooking Dong Khoi street, Saigon Café is one of the best buffet destinations in Saigon since 2003. Offering a vast selection of live cooking and interactive counters, each features an array of theater showcasing an array of hand-crafted dishes ranging from regional cuisines of Vietnam to Chinese, Japanese, Italian, French, Indian and more. description: Host by Chef Hậu and our Monkey. The Monkey Gallery DINING is one of the first fine dining restaurants in Ho Chi Minh City, opening in 2019 with a passion for bringing a new gastronomic destination with a Vietnamese soul to local and international diners. The dining room features an ultra-high ceiling with a central open kitchen that acts as the heart of the gallery, where our artists work on their imaginative creations. description:
Banh mi Huynh Hoa was born in 1989. 

Although banh mi is a easy, popular street food, HuynhHoa attracts to Saigon people, gourmets, and the food blogger community around the world with the high quality of ingredients from bread, cold cuts, butter, fatty pate to cucumbers and pickles, all of which are of high quality and constantly upgraded.

description: Our flagship restaurant Nineteen, named after our address at 19 Lam Son Square, has grown a reputation in Saigon for its unparalleled seafood buffet and five-star dining experience. The seafood is caught fresh from Vietnam’s waters in the East Sea and off the tropical holiday island of Phu Quoc in the southwest. But Nineteen isn’t just about the seafood buffet. Everyday there are breakfast and lunch buffets that include the freshest and best quality produce that can be sourced in Vietnam and from abroad, including mouthwatering roasts, ribs, vegetables and salads. Whether you prefer soup or sushi, pho or pancakes, both Asian and Western options are available for the most discerning eaters to mix things up a bit, all of course, topped off with an indulgent spread of delicious desserts.

description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description: Mặn Mòi serves authentic Vietnamese cuisine, which we relish. Having set foot in foreign lands, we've come to appreciate local, homely dishes even more. This is our reason for opening this bistro to share our love for Vietnamese delicacies with friends worldwide. Let us share a few notes here and there about the origins of our dishes so that your meal takes on this air of leisure. We draw inspiration from the hearty meals our Grandmothers and Mothers prepared and select the freshest local produce to turn into homely dishes, be it a salad, a stew, a soup, or a dessert. We do everything with care because we want to convey the elegance of Vietnamese cuisine and the warm hospitality of Vietnamese people. Please note that we also have a takeaway option. If you can't dine in, ask our staff to wrap savory Saigon delicacies to enjoy at home. May you have a festive meal.

description: Italiani’s specializes in beautifully crafted individual wood fired pizzas and Italian-inspired dishes. We poured our hearts into creating a local Pizzeria that provides exceptional food, a welcoming environment for families and business professionals, and a fun date night spot for couples. We use the most flavorful tomatoes, cheeses and other fresh locally-sourced ingredients when possible to make our wood fired pizzas and Italian-inspired dishes. Our pizza dough is also made with “secret” ingredients that are hand worked and tossed to ensure that our pizzas have a deliciously thin crispy crust, with a chewy center, topped with the freshest ingredients. They are then fired to perfection in our authentic wood fired oven to seal in flavor and transform our menu items into fine crafted masterpieces. Our appetizers, salads, homemade gelato, and local craft beers are just a few more reasons to enjoy a meal at Italiani’s Homemade Pizza.

description: Mặn Mòi serves authentic Vietnamese cuisine, which we relish. Having set foot in foreign lands, we've come to appreciate local, homely dishes even more. This is our reason for opening this bistro to share our love for Vietnamese delicacies with friends worldwide. Let us share a few notes here and there about the origins of our dishes so that your meal takes on this air of leisure. We draw inspiration from the hearty meals our Grandmothers and Mothers prepared and select the freshest local produce to turn into homely dishes, be it a salad, a stew, a soup, or a dessert. We do everything with care because we want to convey the elegance of Vietnamese cuisine and the warm hospitality of Vietnamese people. Please note that we also have a takeaway option. If you can't dine in, ask our staff to wrap savory Saigon delicacies to enjoy at home. May you have a festive meal.

description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description: "Great People Love Great Food" | A Hidden gem famous to the Native Vietnamese, from north to south. Led by owner & Master Chef Quan Diec with over 45 years experience in Traditional Hong Kong style Chinese cuisine & 35 years of Japanese Sushi & Sashimi, located in Saigon's China Town. Our journey began as an outside restaurant since 1999. Yes, outdoor only seating with the little red plastic stools, and the aroma of spit roasted whole cows (Bê Vàng) wafting to the street. Now, transformed and earning a distinguished place in Saigon's social and culinary landscape. We are so proud to offer this unique experience, that showcases our roots deep in the art of traditional Hong Kong Chinese cuisine and Sushi & Sashimi creations that deliver the freshest flavors from the sea. Thriving by staying consistent with what we know. With a menu of over 100 recipes tested over decades, everyone is sure to find something and love what they find. Walk-in’s are available, come see us today!

description: Today With You is a Korean-style pasta restaurant located in the heart of Thao Dien, Ho Chi Minh City. Known for its romantic atmosphere and unique fusion flavors, the restaurant has been featured in several popular Korean media outlets: ✔ Featured on TVN’s “Dokbak Tour” – Ho Chi Minh Episode ✔ Featured on YouTube channels “Vietnam Ttubuck-i” and “Hoonbine” With its deep green color palette, warm wood accents, and charming pink highlights, Today With You offers a cozy and aesthetic dining experience perfect for couples. description: Lai is a new exploration of Modern Cantonese cuisine offering a unique culinary experience. Through a distinctive menu, a dim sum bar selection, and a display of rich sashimi choices, our menu lets the ingredients take the lead. Fresh and imaginative, it invigorates traditional recipes for a modern audience. Our Chefs combine age-old techniques and meaningful flavors with imagination and refinement—the result is flavorful, unexpected, and elegantly executed dishes. description: Our name should not be mistaken to indicate a Street Stall.  We are a sit-down table service Vietnamese Bistro serving authentic Vietnamese Home Cooked meals.  Globally famed and rated Vietnam’s #1 restaurant serving an original 19th Century Banh Mi as introduced to Saigon by French culinary Masters.  Our special charcoal grilled fillings feature imported meats: USDA Choice Steaks, Pork, and Chicken.  A simple one-page menu features our classic Home Cooked Vegan & Non-Vegan favorites: Gluten-free Noodles, Meats, and Vegan Items.  Our global culinary excellence is TV documented by, BBC, Pan Asia Food Review, Moya Moya Japan, along with Vietnamese tour guides: Ctrip Gourmet PRC, Rurubu, Vinadaytravel, Tripzilla, Coconuts, etc. AMBIANCE: Climate controlled, English-speaking servers.  MEALS: delicate garden fresh local herbs and spices. HYGIENE & VALUE: Health-conscious meals offer value for money. Five-star quality at value prices.

Drawing inspiration from the traditional flavors and cultural heritage of the ancient town of Hội An, our restaurant aims to capture the essence of Vietnamese cuisine in a contemporary and inviting setting. description: Dining in Saigon is quite easy and it is not a place where you will easily go hungry, regardless of your budget. description: Cafe de l’Opera is quite possibly in the best location in our city, that’s if you enjoy your views with a dash of history and a slice of modernity all rolled into one. The cafe is located on the ground floor of the hotel on the corner of historic Dong Khoi Street and Lam Son Square, just metres across from Saigon’s iconic municipal theatre, better known as the Opera House. During the day, as temperatures soar and the heavens threaten to open, Cafe de l’Opera becomes a refuge for travellers and the like, just as it always has been since the hotel doors opened in the 50s. Over high-tea, things slow down, friends catch-up, business associates meet and lovers hold hands. By night, things become lively again with tapas, cocktails and wine to the sounds of jazz and the excited chatter of guests enjoying an extended Happy Hour as the city comes alive again.

description: Hola Amigos! This is OUR Tex-Mexican Restaurant in HCMC, Vietnam. I'm (Scott) from Maine, USA & my wife and better half (Duc) is from here in Saigon. What we are trying to do here at La Fiesta is to make some tasty and fairly authentic Tex-Mexican food, served with a smile in a welcoming setting. We make all of our sauces and tortillas onsite, and also use Saigon Tacos locally made Corn Tortillas & Salsa Verde. We take great pride in our work, and strive to do our best to pay attention to detail every single day. It's the little things that count, and that gets lost sometimes. We will all work hard every day to stay on top of our game, and keep you wanting to come back to La Fiesta. Serving tasty Tex-Mex food and drink in the heart of Saigon.

description: At Å by TUNG, savor every moment of the night with Nordic-chic vibes, aurora sky and a sensational dining experience, making the first-of-its-kind debut at the heart of Ho Chi Minh City by the celebrated Head Chef Hoang Tung, the youngest Vietnamese Chef to rank in the TOP 100 of THE ASIA’S 50 BEST RESTAURANTS list at the age of 28. In 2022, Hoang Tung joined FORBES UNDER 30, 2022, as the fearless pioneer of tasting menu in Vietnam, who set a cornerstone for the new era’s Vietnamese fine dining. A tribute to Northern Europe where Chef Tung’s passion for fine culinary blossomed, the restaurant offers bespoke guests a frontrow view of immersive Nordic interiors and a celebration of flavours, seasonality and aesthetics, across its signature 20-course tasting menu. Constantly innovative and occasionally rebellious, beyond introducing signature dishes, Hoang Tung and his team is passionate to invoke a sense of wonders in each and every guest and deliver an original, authentic experience

description: San Fu Lou_ The house of three blessings. At our restaurant, we provide great tasty food, healthy cooking techniques and hygiene. At SFL, we take the traditional concept of a Chinese kitchen and bring it to a new level of sophistication with a contemporary Oriental ambience replete with the colours and material of a traditional Chinese "house". Our show kitchen, which is a first in Vietnam for a Chinese restaurant, allows diners to take in a visual feast before the food is served. This kitchen shows the guests the extensive Chinese influences which can be found in the Vietnamese culinary heritage today.These include the use of bean curd, stir-frying food, the use of chop-stick and wok, and so much more. SFL is a place to enjoy Chinese classics with handpicked teas and allows all guests to appreciate nostalgic tastes in these modern times.

description: At Dalcheeni we serve you a part of our culture ,soaked in our heritage ,made with heart and served with passion . description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description: Benthanh Princess is a luxurious dining cruise offering unique culinary and sightseeing experiences. It is also recognized as the ideal venue for the most upscale and elegant events on the Saigon River. A French Brasserie and Wine Bar tucked away in a secluded courtyard in the heart of the city, The Refinery offers a terrace with comfy armchairs and a beautiful interior with many original architectural features. description: The Propaganda menu, with its fresh spring rolls, noodle salads & crunchy rice bowls features simple yet amazingly flavourful food prepared with the freshest local goods. Think 100% local, envision “redesigned” home cooking, all with Vietnamese ingredients only, home-baked bread for the banh mis, home-made tofu (with and without egg), home-made ice-cream, home-made soya milk, home-made everything! The propaganda art on the walls is a take on a very local art form that came to life in the 1940's. Our mural was commissioned by us and designed by a local artist. It is a happy rendering of the Vietnamese country and city life. Our cushions, bench seats and napkins are in tune and make the experience complete, an immersion into a Vietnam gone by...

description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description: La Cuisine is a French restaurant located in the heart of Ho Chi Minh city, designed to make you feel as if you were at home. The open kitchen gives you the opportunity to see the Chef and his team pamper you with a selection of mouth-watering dishes. Having worked in France, London, and São Paulo, Chef Erwann Serene decided to settle in Vietnam where he worked in La Camargue for the past 8 years. In 2009, he decides to open his own restaurant, and works on the La Cuisine concept, which is a mix of a home designed kitchen and trendy restaurant serving refined Mediterranean Cuisine. “Visit La Cuisine for a fantastic, reasonably priced lunch set or for a sumptuous dinner, be sure to make a reservation as word about this wonderful eatery has spread like wildfire”. Gourmet Vietnam Magazine 2010-2011

description: “Vị Sài Gòn” – a warm house that harmonizes many nuances of flavors and emotions, gathering the essence of Vietnamese ingredients combined with new experiences from the flow of diverse cultural intersections on this land. At “Vị Sài Gòn”, each dish echoes the whispers of the long-standing culinary heritage and carries its own story told through flavors. From the harmonious tastes of the North to the rich and bold flavors of the Central region, along with the delicate flavors of Southern cuisine to the modern culinary techniques of international cuisine – all are meticulously and perfectly blended! We believe that cuisine is not only a passion but also a bridge connecting people. With the mission of creating unique culinary experiences, “Vị Saigon” is an unmissable destination for those who are passionate about exploring and experiencing culinary culture in Saigon – the city full of emotions!

description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description: Level 1 & 2 offers a full day dining experience as it opens its doors from 08:00 Am for breakfast/ Coffee and continues on for lunch and entertains last order for dinner at 02.00 Am. Diners have the option to dine in non-smoking airconditioned area and an outdoor alfresco at level 1 and a balcony view on level 2 that has a view like no other. The surprise comes after 10.30pm when levels 1 & 2 transform into a music bar that feeds your soul with songs from the 70’s - 80’s that plays in the background as you enjoy conversations or choose to sing and dance along to your favorite songs. Level 3 is a Rooftop bar which opens at 4 pm for Happy Hour till 6pm. Place for those who want to impress or be impressed. Reservations are recommended to avoid disappointment.

description: Ten floors above the heart of the city, Saigon Saigon Rooftop Bar is an iconic, inviting space to share a drink, soak up sunset views, or unwind with live music and good company. Since 1959, the bar has drawn people from all over the world to its open-air tables and breezy verandah. Saigon Saigon played a prominent role as a haven for wartime journalists in the 1960s. The heritage wall along the staircase leading to the entrance highlights pivotal moments in Caravelle history.

description: Terra means “Earth”, Viva means “praise of life”. Terraviva is a living breathing earth, breathing the breath of life into all its creatures in perfect harmony and fertility. The name Terraviva means “innocent and fresh spirit”. Terraviva also reminds us that keeping the connection between us as humans and all other beings on this fragile planet. We consider food as a gift from Mother Nature and not only is fresh food an essential part of living healthy, but it can also be a delicious meal to enjoy our daily life. It’s moment when we sit together as friends and family to share a meal, that’s when we can appreciate life a whole lot more. We at Terraviva have respect for our fragile wonderful earth and it’s gifts ,we believe life is about always doing what we can in limiting waste in business and daily life, whether that’s shopping locally,planting more trees, reuse, reduce or recycling or simply cherishing the food we consume. And pulling together as a community We invite you to visit Terraviva, to enjoy delicious dishes made from traditional Italian cuisine- baked to perfection by an 20-year experience Italian chef and the delightful flavors from Mother Earth in a cozy, friendly atmosphere with exceptional service. Terraviva Pizza & Italian Cuisine - flavors from the Earth

description: We are serious about the term Mediterranean here. We don’t just mean Italian & Greek delicacies, we mean Mediterranean in the wide sense; Turkey, Cyprus, Lebanon, Syria, Israel, Egypt, Algeria, Morocco, Spain, etc. We selected wines in harmony with our food and snack menus. Our charming colonial building with no frills, original cement tiles, bare brick walls and old window frames is ideally located half way between the Reunification Palace and Notre-Dame. The space has a peaceful, relaxed feel to it and is a perfect stop on a busy day around the city with a small but extremely popular terrace on Saigon’s most prestigious tree lined street. We are opened for breakfast, lunch and dinner. A super popular brunch is served from 11 to 4 Saturday and Sunday (bookings highly recommended). As demonstrated by our bikes zipping around the city, our delivery service is the most efficient and most popular in the city, amongst expats and locals alike. Au Parc opened in February 2003.

description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description: La Crêperie is a casual French bistro, already famous in various big cities in Asia. Besides some traditional French dishes, you will find here the most authentic French savory and sweet crêpes. Wether you have a sweet tooth or not, with so many options in the menu, you will for sure find your favorite. In addition, specifically in Ho Chi Minh City, our Chef proposes some great Pizza, with a wonderful bread made thin and crispy, to let you enjoy our great selection of toppings. La Crêperie is not only a place serving great food. It is a place you may also enjoy for its atmosphere, thanks to a nice decoration and an attentive team, managed by Patrice, the owner of the place, who will warmly welcome you!

description: Host by Chef Hậu and our Monkey. The Monkey Gallery DINING is one of the first fine dining restaurants in Ho Chi Minh City, opening in 2019 with a passion for bringing a new gastronomic destination with a Vietnamese soul to local and international diners. The dining room features an ultra-high ceiling with a central open kitchen that acts as the heart of the gallery, where our artists work on their imaginative creations. The 200m² area has 12 seats, 7 chef's table seats, and a Private Gallery, all designed for the best comfort to enjoy the chef’s creativity. The Monkey Gallery DINING has received Michelin-selected awards for 2023 and 2024, the Best 50 Discovery award, and Tripadvisor’s Traveller Choice 2023.

description:
Established in 2018, come experience Saigon's most unique sushi omakase by Chef Murata Shinji. The chef's choice (omakase) menu at Kasen pairs the highest quality, seasonal ingredients with modern, refined preparations all the while holding roots to washoku tradition. Kasen emphasizes each ingredients peak flavor and  clean, minimal aesthetics (never any distractions). Enjoy Chef Murata's cuisine with premium selections of Japanese sake, exceptional boutique wines, and creative  cocktails. Menus change weekly dependent on international fish market availabllity. And ingredients are sourced globally to showcase the season's best from Japan, France, Spain, Australia and New Zealand.

Reservation and counter seating suggested for omakase. Private room available for parties up to 12 persons. Advanced boookings are highly recommended.

description: If there is anything to conclude about Vietnamese food, it can only be the "unpredictable diversity". Each region- North, Central and South has something to be proud of. The influence of Chinese and French culture during colonial time adds more to the vibrant scenes of gastronomy. It is hard to describe and compare the specific features of cuisines from each region as there is more than a capital of food in Vietnam. While Hanoi offers some authentic and original food experience, Hue boasts about its royal trait and Ho Chi Minh City is proud that it is the most inclusive place when it comes to dining. You will have to discover it yourself, visit Quan Bui restaurants and decide which one you like the most!

Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description: A chic and intimate space living up to its name. This is one of the best spots in Sai Gon to enjoy drinks as the sun sets over Park and Ben Thanh Market. Offering 270-degree city views, the environment created is the best of all worlds. Luxuriously high enough up to delight in exquisitely romantic views of Park in its entirety, yet close enough to feel at eye level and at one with the city streets and rooftops. Beautifully and atmospherically designed – glass, metal and wood complement a monochromatic color palate of black, granite grey and hints of cream. description: Italiani’s specializes in beautifully crafted individual wood fired pizzas and Italian-inspired dishes. We poured our hearts into creating a local Pizzeria that provides exceptional food, a welcoming environment for families and business professionals, and a fun date night spot for couples. We use the most flavorful tomatoes, cheeses and other fresh locally-sourced ingredients when possible to make our wood fired pizzas and Italian-inspired dishes. Our pizza dough is also made with “secret” ingredients that are hand worked and tossed to ensure that our pizzas have a deliciously thin crispy crust, with a chewy center, topped with the freshest ingredients. They are then fired to perfection in our authentic wood fired oven to seal in flavor and transform our menu items into fine crafted masterpieces. Our appetizers, salads, homemade gelato, and local craft beers are just a few more reasons to enjoy a meal at Italiani’s Homemade Pizza.

description: Inspired by the restaurant “La Pointe Des Blagueurs”, then the café “Jokers’ Point”, built in the same place at Bach Dang harbor - a popular destination of Saigon during the country’s tumultuous 1950s, after nearly 7 decades, ROS was established and revivified in 2019. Building on the history of the area while sewing ourselves into the fabric of future gives us the opportunity to become a gatekeeper to the city – a key player in Saigon’s food and drink scene. ROS is a day-to-night, Pan-Asian restaurant with nautical vibes and a hint of Cote d’Azur style. More than just an exquisite meal with a panoramic riverfront view, dining experience at ROS meant to engage all of the senses by offering a chance to savor an innovative Pan-Asian cuisine, sip on a range of exotic cocktails, and immerse yourself in the serenity of Saigon river.

description: Une Journée à Paris is a traditional French bakery and patisserie, proudly French owned and operated. Neighboring the iconic Ben Thanh market, our bakery attracts both local and international foodies alike. We are passionate about offering all of our visitors an authentic taste of Paris. We believe that Paris has not passed your lips until you’ve had a bite of one of our croissants, chouquettes, or religieuses. Our macarons are adored far and wide, with orders coming in from Singapore, Malaysia and Hong Kong. For an original recipe, our mango pies, rum babas, or edelweiss are for you. All of our pastries, cakes and bites in-between are made with quality goods. We use European imported ingredients to give you an experience that ticks the boxes of quality, taste, and authenticity. As French we stay true to tradition, and prefer to use the recipes found in our grandmothers kitchens. We look forward to sharing these with you!

description: The mind is a wondrous place. It contains our memories, talents, and perceptions, but we can sometimes get lost in the the complications life brings. In Buddhism, every sentient being has a mind of its own and there exists a pure primordial energy in each of us; this state of purity is what Buddhist practitioners seek to reach through meditation. At Shamballa, we are inspired by Tibetan Buddhism and the teachings about the mind. We wanted to create a space where the mind can unwind in a serene atmosphere. Our vegetarian cuisine accommodates the experience by providing delicate flavour combinations for the palate. We organically produce some of our own vegetables, and we carefully select others to ensure you dine on the finest ingredients. We hope you enjoy your meal with us, and we hope you leave our new wondrous home, located in the heart of Saigon, feeling brighter than before.

description: A sense of Indochina located in the heart of the city Inspired by the movie “Indochine” by director Regis Wargnier, the Indochine Restaurant was opened right in the heart of a bustling street, yet still remains its isolated nature. Leaving behind any daily worries, customers will go on a pleasant journey as soon as he or she step into the grandiose old 19th century villa – where Indochine Saigon is located. Following the unique and excellent design, the Indochine Restaurant is skillfully divided into different room sections, from the separate cozy dining rooms to spacious and elegant ones, as if to bring customers back to the old Saigon. The beautiful garden adorned with a “cloud-shape” lake which is skillfully made by master craftsmen is eminently suitable for any outdoor parties or events. A beautiful and elegant designed public bar with dozens of types of drinks made from Vietnamese traditional fruit would bring great joy to any customer. With a wealth of experience and passion in their expertise, chefs in Indochine Restaurant have spent an adequate time to visit any corner of this country to discover, experience and, literally cook with regional inhabitants. From what they have experienced, chefs in Indochine Restaurant will capture the very essence of every meal they have tried and create such an extensive and colorful menu that we currently have. Customers can detect distinguishing smell and taste of different unique meals which could only be found in this restaurant. With the above special features, Indochine Restaurant would present the perfect choice to anyone who has a savor in Vietnamese cuisine

description: Akuna, located at the Le Méridien Saigon, sits in full view of the Saigon River and is led by Chef Sam Aisbett and hospitality veteran Desiderio Bevilaqua. Bringing his rule-breaking nature to the kitchen, Sam actively decides against limiting the menus to the boundaries of a region or style. With a nod to the people and produce of Vietnam, guests can expect indigenous ingredients, local herbs and spices, rare flavours and nuances — many of which find their way to a fine dining menu for the very first time. The dining experience is further enhanced by a wine list that features a variety of natural, organic and iconic wine bottles; and a cocktail menu of reinvented classics.

description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

Her key childhood memories are her childhood Vietnamese meals, the fierce and strict mothers who raise their children with discipline , the stuffy ao dai fashion stores, the old 80s gadgets..all you can experience in the cozy area of Bep Me In. Here, visitors will enjoy authentic iconic vietnamese food all over the country.

description: At Union Jack’s we like the simple things in life – calm seas and a piping hot plate of fish & chips. We are here to bring authentic British food to your belly. Union Jack's is the quintessential British Fish & Chips restaurant in the heart of District 1 in Ho Chi Minh city. Famous for the "Best Fish & Chips in Saigon - if not Vietnam" while also serving the best of British with a few Irish and Australian favourites. A good selection of Vegetarian and a few Vegan options, too. Homemade sauces, perfect crisp batter, banging bangers and marvelous mash. Beef & Ale Stew that tastes like Grandmas! Come, let your senses set sail back to Britain. Come aboard! Join the fish & chip union. #JoinTheUnion #UnionJacksFishandChips

description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description: District Federal is an authentic Mexican restaurant, bringing flavors & tastes from DF (Mexico City). At DF, we make our own masa from yellow corn, for our tortillas, tacos, tostadas and chips. We make homemade fresh cheese (Queso Fresco), Mexican Crema and all other sauces, salsas and marinates. Our chef, Victor, hails from Mexico City and he brings years of Mexican culinary experience with him to Vietnam. Our menu, whilst offering authentic Mexican cuisine, also caters for the less authentic "Tex Mex" styles of dishes, in order for us to satisfy diverse tastes and experiences. Along with traditional, tacos, tostadas, quesadillas and enchiladas, we have an extensive chargrill section on our menu, of Carne Asada, ribs, wings, fajitas, octopus and squid. We have an extensive vibrant bar with fresh juice Patron Tequila margaritas, spirits and beers. At DF, we have created a fun and lively dining experience, with authentic Mexican cuisine, awesome drinks and cool Latino tunes.

description: The beginning of BASTA HiRo goes back 28 years ago to the legendary Italian restaurant named BASTA PASTA in Harajuku Jinjumae. BASTA PASTA was the first of its kind with an open kitchen in the center of the restaurant, which placed the spotlight on the chef. The head chef of this restaurant was master chef Hiromi YAMADA who led the culture of Italian cuisine in Japan. This restaurant literally ignited the Itameshi ("Ita" is short for "Italian" and "meshi" is the Japanese colloquial equivalent for "food") boom in Japan.

description: Located in Saigon, THE BRIX restaurant and bar lounge offers a slice of paradise mere minutes away from the heart of the city. This small oasis is in an outdoor environment and combines a swimming pool, restaurant and bar – all surrounded by an extensive tropical garden. During the day, it is a peaceful hideaway where you can swim, eat, sip and relax on a daybed under the shade of swaying palms. Over the evening, the venue transforms into an enchanting and intimate restaurant for dinner. On the weekends you can enjoy the vibrant late night atmosphere accompanied with music curated by our DJs or live bands. Whether it’s – a chilled bottle of wine, bespoke cocktails, fresh seafood, or anything else from Chef Phong’s inventive Western fusion menu, THE BRIX has you covered. Escape the mundane and step into our tropical oasis.

description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description: More than 25 years serving the gourmet of Sai Gon, Din Ky Nguyen Trai (DKNT) - a member of Din Ky Group - has become a familiar destination referring to Saigon Cuisine (Saigon is former name of Ho Chi Minh City) With 24/7 continuous operation service, at any time of the day, DKNT’s customers can freely choose from over 400 TASTY & HEALTHY dishes are cooked elaborately and harmoniously combined style of European-Asian-Vietnamese-Chinese cuisine When persons are talking about DKNT, as mentioned above, gourmet immediately think of fish fillet, hand-pulled noodle or Hong Kong Dimsum in the morning, Vietnamese cuisine at noon and superb delicacies which are made from fresh seafood at night. Operating under the model of the restaurant, but DKNT always imbues with intimacy and its own cozy. When you come here, it is not difficult to meet diners customers of all ages. They can be the old mans, the silver-haired old ladies or the baby babbling. They gather, talk and share food and drink at DKNT as at their own small house. Let's visit Din Ky Nguyen Trai once, you will feel its beauty, its unique and the food of this place where no place can have it. Din Ky Nguyen Trai

description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description: Blanc. Restaurant employs a team of deaf and hearing impaired staff. We invite you to try a new dining experience, where communicating with your server may not be as simple as opening your mouth to speak. Our lives consist of the sounds that we hear. We are controlled by sounds, from clocks and phones, and from voices. We react strongly and swiftly to the words of others, and expect the same in return. But what if this ability was taken away? What if your word would be silent? What if your spoken words will not be understood? Does food taste or smell better in silent surrounding? Would I experience a heightened sense of taste? The service team at Blanc. uses Ho Chi Minh City Sign Language which is one of the three Vietnamese Sign Languages, which is influenced by American Sign Language or ASL and French Sign Language (Langue des Signes Française) or LSF. In the menu and on the cheat-sheet you will find signs that are useful to give sign language a try! Of course pen and paper are at hand if needed. Should we remain quiet during the meal, you may ask? No, you do not have to remain quiet during your meal. Due to the atmosphere and interactions with our wait staff, you may find yourself lowering your voice, but you do not have to remain silent during your meal. Just laugh, share and have a good time.

description: Nang Ganh is the first crowd-funding restaurant built by 160 Facebookers. It is really a beautiful story of start-up business. The owner created delivery service named Ganh Hang Rong 4 years ago which is developing day by day and become one of the biggest catering service in Vietnamese traditional foods. The food, the service and the story life of the owner are the key factors to attract guests. The owner is also the main cooker: she puts all her passion in cooking and decorating each dish. She is devoted at doing customer service and so strong in details. She can meet all the difficult requirements provided that it is Vietnamese food. You can enjoy the food on the banana leaf with bamboo tray that is unique vs other places. You also feel comfortable with the ambience of the French antique villa which is attractive with most of people come here. We serve a-la-carte on normal days and buffet on Saturday. We are strong at holding wedding ceremony, birthday parties, events, seminars, meetings, conferences, etc... We supply the A-Z services from F&B and decoration to the specific theme, music band, meeting facilities, MC, entertainment activities. It's our big honor to welcome you in NangGanh Restaurant- the unique Vietnamese cuisine restaurant.

description: Amun is a wonderful place to look at least once in your life. It is filled up with the fragrance of Mediterranean Sea spices and has everything you need for a swell time. Bang on!! Our restaurant is popular for delicious Moroccan Traditional Food. If you’re craving something warm and hearty, consider whipping up this Mediterranean stew. The harissa, cumin, coriander and cinnamon create an out-of-this-world flavor that goes deliciously with the kinds of meat and Israeli couscous The collection of varieties wine of many countries is offered to boost up your dining experience. Get the popular homemade signature cocktails and soft drinks like Moroccan mint tea, hot and cold drinks according to your order. For a lot of Shisha lover in the HCMC, there is no better way to wind down than in a cloud of sweet-smelling smoke with a shisha or hookah pipe in hand. Now, combine that with mouth-watering food and superb service — your weekends are sure to be a blast

description: Indika: House of Curiosity A hidden gem within the hustle and bustle of Saigon. Indika is a unique place for drinks, music, food and good vibes since 2016. A secret garden and artistic interior painted and decorated with treasures and gems collected by the owners who made this place so special - A hub for Saigon’s artistic community with weekly open mics, musical jams, Indika showcases some great original live music, comedy, and poetry in the city. On the weekend, DJs fill the space with Reggae, Hip Hop, Disco, Funk, Soul, Tropical and more, including special Vinyl Selectors At the bar you can get awesome looking and tasting signature and classic cocktails, mixed, shaken and stirred by passionate bartenders. On top of a great selection of wines, craft beers & ciders, spirits and Indika’s Special Home Made Rum Punch On the menu, there’s a wide selection of food as there are currently 3 restaurants - Indika Kitchen, Organik Kitchen and Drunk Tacos. Serving meat, vegan, gluten free.

description: Hủ Tiếu Hồng Phát has been serving for nearly 50 years and has become one of the oldest and most beloved culinary brands in Saigon. With its special recipe, Hong Phat has maintained a strong impression on the people of Saigon through generations of customers. As the culinary service industry continues to develop, Hồng Phát constantly adjusts and improves to meet the high service standards. It not only focuses on the quality of the cuisine, but also creates a comfortable space to ensure that every guest has a sastisfied experiences while dining with us. The year 2023 marked a special milestone for us as we received the Bib Gourmand award from the prestigious culinary magazine The Michelin Guide, organized for the first time in Vietnam. With a firm commitment to development and quality improvement, Hồng Phát aims not only to bring delicious dishes to the Vietnamese community but also to share with international diners.

description: Host by Chef Hậu and our Monkey. The Monkey Gallery DINING is one of the first fine dining restaurants in Ho Chi Minh City, opening in 2019 with a passion for bringing a new gastronomic destination with a Vietnamese soul to local and international diners. The dining room features an ultra-high ceiling with a central open kitchen that acts as the heart of the gallery, where our artists work on their imaginative creations. The 200m² area has 12 seats, 7 chef's table seats, and a Private Gallery, all designed for the best comfort to enjoy the chef’s creativity. The Monkey Gallery DINING has received Michelin-selected awards for 2023 and 2024, the Best 50 Discovery award, and Tripadvisor’s Traveller Choice 2023.

description: Lost in Saigon is a funky cocktail bar and restaurant on the busy Bui Vien street. We have full Vietnamese and Western menu including burgers, pizza, steak, Mexican burritos and fajitas, plus we cater for vegetarians as well. Sit inside in the air conditioning or sit outside on our comfy chairs where it is perfect for people watching. There is always something happening on Bui Vien! Lost in Saigon is proud to only use the highest quality ingredients. Our steak comes from Australia, our salmon from Norway, and our vegetables are sourced fresh daily direct from the farmers market. Please also come try our shisha, we only use genuine tobacco imported from Middle East and our staff are experts in making the perfect flavor combinations. We only use the highest quality alcohol in our cocktails. For example we only use Captain Morgan in our Mojito's, and you can choose from Hendricks, Tanqueray, Bombay Sapphire or Gordon's for your Gin and Tonic. We are confident our food, shisha, and cocktails are the best in Bui Vien and we hope to help you find yourself Lost in Saigon soon!

Yakuzen is a member of Rohto-Mentholatum (Vietnam), embodying the happiness, health, and prosperity that Rohto-Mentholatum (Vietnam) aims to bring. Come by, grab a seat (or take it to go), and enjoy the warmth of homemade food with a local touch!

description: ABOUT US Hong Hai seafood restaurant has been well known over 20 years for its fine seafood cuisine since it started as a small family restaurant in district 2. Now located at 236 Pasteur - District 3 - HCM City, the elegant 3-story restaurant with accommodation of over 500 guests attracts a sophisticated crowd to its modern yet cozy ambiance. Plus, with private rooms, Hong Hai is a perfect place for family and company’s meeting or party. Run by the family matriarch, known by her frequent customers as “ Co Nam”, Hong Hai proudly invites you to enjoy its delectable dishes, which prepared by cherished family recipes. Have you tried Grilled Fresh Oyster with cheese, or Hong Hai Special fried rice with crabmeat, or Grilled Fresh Red Fish with Salt and Chilli, etc…? If not, let Hong Hai’s chefs surprise you with our culinary creative while maintaining integrity of ingredients with specialty dishes.

description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description: VIETNAMESE GOURMET Cocochin is a part of the Saigon House, located on the city’s most crowded Nguyen Hue Pedestrian Street. The 400 seat restaurant has wide airy space of 1,000 square metre on two floors of dining space architecture reminiscing the beloved homeland of Vietnam. Cocochin gives diners the opportunity to experience the essence of the renowned cuisine brands from the North - Central - South regions with many appealing dishes: . The delicacy of dishes from the North like Bun Dau (Fermented shrimp paste with fried tofu and rice vermicelli), Pho Cuon (Fresh Rice Noodle Rolls), Cha Com (Sweet rice flake meatballs), Nem Phung (Phung fermented pork) of the Alley 89 in Ha Noi. • The tasty of dishes from the Central like Cao Lau (a regional Vietnamese dish made with noodles, pork, and local greens, that is found only in the town of Hoi An), Bun Ca Ngu (Tuna with Vermicelli Soup), Cha Khoai (Khoai grilled chopped fish) from Quan Gi Do Restaurant, Bep nha Xu Quang Restaurant - Da Nang, and Khoai Restaurant - Nha Trang . • The abundance of dishes from the South like Com Tam Bui (broken rice and grilled pork chops), Oc Dao (dishes from snails), Bun Mam Khanh Hoi (Rice Vermicelli Soup with Fermented Fish and Seafood), Hu Tieu Chu Tu Gia (rice noodle with pork and seafood), Banh Khot Banh Xeo Co Ba Vung Tau (Vietnamese crispy rice pancakes with seafood), goi cuon (fresh spring rolls) of Vietnamese Bistro, vegetarian dishes of Chai Vegetarian; Red Desert Factory’s, and Snowee’s desert cakes, ice creams, and sweeties, and others. Especially, Cocochin serves unique dishes from two famous Asian cuisines -- Japan - Haha Sushi & Thai - Thai Malee.

description: Le Bourgeois Restaurant was the most favorite rendezvous of Graham Greene during his stay in Saigon. In the old time, politicians, correspondents and journalists gathered to discuss political issues in "cafe the la hien", a casual name of this restaurant. Nowadays, the former saying "if the walls of the restaurant could talk, they would tell you many secrets" is still the start of all discussion about this restaurant. Le Bourgeois Restaurant today is luxury dining with classic style decoration, that serves western cuisine. The restaurant is located on the ground floor of the hotel, overlooking the Opera House and is conveniently accessible for both in-house and walk-in guests. In the morning, guests can choose either Vietnamese breakfast dishes with variety of noodles or Continental breakfast (bread, butter, jam...). Lunch and dinner is the time for our guests to enjoy Western cuisine along with elegant classic melodies of Piano and Violin.

description: Host by Chef Hậu and our Monkey. The Monkey Gallery DINING is one of the first fine dining restaurants in Ho Chi Minh City, opening in 2019 with a passion for bringing a new gastronomic destination with a Vietnamese soul to local and international diners. The dining room features an ultra-high ceiling with a central open kitchen that acts as the heart of the gallery, where our artists work on their imaginative creations. The 200m² area has 12 seats, 7 chef's table seats, and a Private Gallery, all designed for the best comfort to enjoy the chef’s creativity. The Monkey Gallery DINING has received Michelin-selected awards for 2023 and 2024, the Best 50 Discovery award, and Tripadvisor’s Traveller Choice 2023.

description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description: Located in “Le Gendamerier Coloniale” building on De La Grandière Street now Lý Tự Trọng, Bebop is an “ordinary” wine bar. description: Ichihana Sushi specializes in modern Japanese cuisine & premium omakase sushi buffet. We offer dine in, take out & delivery, and catering service. We are committed to providing our customers with the finest level of hospitality. From the moment you walk through our doors, you will be greeted by our staff and treated warmly, promptly, and graciously throughout your meal. Ichihana Sushi commits to choosing and using clean, quality ingredients and fresh seafood to combine and create the restaurant's unique dishes, but still maintain an affordable price for our customers. By sticking with our slogan "Fine and Fresh", we make sure that you leave our restaurant satisfied and with a smile. description: Our story is as old as it is new - embrace a cuisine influenced by ancient Arabic and Mediterranean cultures and create fresh, new flavor profiles. Ras el hanout is an essential ingredient and we use over 20 different spices to create our own blend. It gives foods fragrant, aromatic and warmly spiced flavors that Moroccan dishes are renown for. Breakfast, lunch or dinner, it's a great place for chilling out with a pot of Moroccan mint or selection of fruit teas and coffees. A chill bar that offers up our signature cocktails like the dusty camel, Rick’s Cafe Americain and Ilsa’s Choice. Casablanca never had it so good. We welcome you to discover classic and contemporary fare. We hope you enjoy our take on a timeless cuisine. It’s the beginning of a beautiful friendship.

description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description: May you come hungry, eat plenty, drink perhaps a bit too much and always enjoy the experience. Inspired by the tapas tradition and its ability to bring people together, Ria was created out of a passion for Spanish food, drinks and culture. Our aim is to be rooted in tradition, heavily influenced by global cuisine with sustainable local market driven fare. Our Spanish Chef, Sergio Nieto Garcés, brings big ideas to small food in our kitchen every day. Gastronomy is in his blood, he was very young when he had his first contact with the kitchen, in his family restaurant, and learnt the classic recipes from his grandfather. Years later he specialized in the modern Spanish cuisine working with the prestigious chef Martín Berasategui (chef with the highest number of Michelin Stars in Spain and 4th in the world). Thanks to his background he proudly combines tradition and vanguard.

description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description: The First Steakhouse is the creation of Chef Danny Duy, a young phenomenon in the Vietnamese culinary scene. Chef Danny Duy has been working in the food business for 15 years, with experience of 7 years working in Singapore at Raffles Inn, Pregro Italian Restaurant, Grill-out Steakhouse, Fullerton… His passion to bring authentic European cuisine to the Vietnam inspired him to start The First. With a breadth of knowledge in both Eastern and Western cuisines, he understands and uses an extensive plethora of ingredients, formulating unique flavor combinations across all of the dishes. Therefore, at The First you get the best of both worlds: the bold flavor palette of the East, and the respect of good ingredients of the West. The First brings you fine dining without a fuss, in a casual yet sophisticated dining atmosphere in the heart of downtown Saigon.

description: Located on the eighth floor of Homestead Parkview, Parkview Restaurant delivers contemporary dining experience with a stunning 270 degree view of the HCMC skyline. Parkview Restaurant features an outdoor setting with a garden like ambiance. A respite from Ho Chi Minh's heat and humidity. description: Peaceful greetings from Đu Đủ Xanh . Green Papaya! At the House of Đu Đủ, we love to welcome you to a nostalgic space, filled with pocket of natural light and green plants. We hope that this place and its peaceful aesthetics will touch you at all your senses – so that when you taste, look, hear, smell, at our house, you will entirely feel “filled” (Đủ). Our menu offers delightful vegetarian and vegan dishes, from selected natural ingredients, definitely no MSG and cooked by a team of passionate chefs. The menu is inspired by the diverse culinary base from Vietnam and other wonderful regional places. For we believe, that going vegetarian is a way to feel the peace, mindfulness and calm from inside - to be here and now - and to be “filled” (Đủ). Grow the Green inside You

description:
Buffet Poseidon is the largest chain of hotpot, BBQ, and seafood buffet restaurants in Vietnam. Inspired by Poseidon, the Greek god of the sea, the brand is dedicated to bringing a diverse and exquisite culinary experience to all diners.  

At Poseidon, guests can enjoy a lavish selection of over 200 meticulously crafted dishes, with premium seafood as the highlight, including crabs, lobsters, mantis shrimp, sea snails, salmon, shrimp, squid, and many more delicacies.  

Diners are invited to indulge in an unlimited feast, featuring a fusion of Asian and European flavors, expertly prepared by top-tier chefs, ensuring an unforgettable gourmet experience.

description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description: Dau Homemade includes a chain of diners that specialize in "bún đậu mắm tôm" (fermented shrimp paste with deep fried tofu and rice vermicelli) and other Hanoi's specialty. The word "homemade" not only means the freshness of the dishes, but also aims to bring customer the feeling of authenticity as they are enjoying the meals in the atmosphere and culture of Hanoi - the north of Vietnam, right in Ho Chi Minh City. Dau Homemade wishes to guide customer from daily normal dishes in every northern Vietnamese family to fascinating and surprising light meals and street food in Hanoi, in the most original and authentic ways. Together with the dishes, the space and decoration here also makes customers feel like travelling among the narrow and ancient street of Hanoi. Moreover, if you are lucky enough, you will find surprise as you are enjoying acoustic music or special shows while you are treating yourself here! Come to Dau Homemade, and taste the authentic culture right at your dish!

description:
Discover the Art of Steak at MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE

Tucked away on a quiet street in the heart of District 3, MRSIMPLE STEAKHOUSE offers an elegant yet welcoming dining experience with a focus on European-inspired cuisine. Known for its tender, flavorful steaks, house-made sauces, and beautifully plated side dishes, MRSIMPLE brings both quality and value to the table.

Whether you’re enjoying a cozy dinner for two, celebrating a special occasion, or gathering with friends, our candlelit setting, warm lighting, and attentive service make every visit feel special. The menu also features fresh pasta, salads, and a curated wine list to complete the perfect meal.

Open for lunch and dinner — and just minutes from downtown Saigon — MRSIMPLE is a hidden gem worth discovering.

description: We are Pham Viet Chanh's premier Omakase Sushi experience located on the top floor of the Lotus Building. Pham Viet Chanh street is located in Binh Thanh District and is sometimes referred to as Ho Chi Minh City's second Little Japan Town apart from Le Thanh Ton and Thai Van Lung's full-blown version. Sharing a penthouse space with the famous Yakitori Hachibei (known for their delicious charcoal grilled meats) and a full bar providing drinks for both venues, Omakase Tiger is an 8-seat counter in front of one of the most recognizable faces of Japan Town, Chef Hiro. Reserve your seats now to experience the exploding charisma of Chef Hiro and his Sous, Chef Chien, as they sculpt and mold the perfect seafood set with an amazing skyline view.

description: VESPER is an intimate and sophisticated destination for great cocktails and fine food. Chef Andreas Ertle has used his years of experience in Michelin star kitchens across the world to create a menu that is unparalleled in Ho Chi Minh City. From Asian inspired Tapas for light and easy dinners to great steaks, pastas and salads for those seeking a more substantial meal. description: RRbar is a trendy and stylish lobby bar and lounge; inspired by the look and feel of a European street-side café. From delicious breakfast pastries in the morning to delicious éclairs and other snacks to leisurely afternoon teas, the innovative menu is designed for comfort and convenience – whether joining us for a meal or grabbing a quick bite to take away. Whether our guests feel like a world-class international wine or award-winning Pasteur Street Brewery craft beer, the drink selection will surprise and delight even veteran bar explorers. Ideal for both casual drinks after a long day of business meetings or an overdue catch-up with friends, Rbar sets a new standard for lounge bars in Saigon.

description: Host by Chef Hậu and our Monkey. The Monkey Gallery DINING is one of the first fine dining restaurants in Ho Chi Minh City, opening in 2019 with a passion for bringing a new gastronomic destination with a Vietnamese soul to local and international diners. The dining room features an ultra-high ceiling with a central open kitchen that acts as the heart of the gallery, where our artists work on their imaginative creations. The 200m² area has 12 seats, 7 chef's table seats, and a Private Gallery, all designed for the best comfort to enjoy the chef’s creativity. The Monkey Gallery DINING has received Michelin-selected awards for 2023 and 2024, the Best 50 Discovery award, and Tripadvisor’s Traveller Choice 2023.

description: Le Café des Stagiaires, with a rooftop over the Saigon River, is the first bar in Vietnam to serve Duvel Moortgat Brewery's portfolio, the iconic Belgian beer company. Good drinks and great food is always the best match! We offer a full European menu, emphasizing the tradition of sharing food - with a French and Belgian focus. At night, the tables make way for a dance floor – while leaving the lounge sofa in the corner for those who prefer to chill.
